  "prompt": "What is a list of superforecasters?",
  "response": "There isn't a single definitive, official list of superforecasters, but some well-known superforecasters have been identified through Philip Tetlock's Good Judgment Project, including:\n\n1. Doug Hubbard\n2. Annie Duke\n3. Warren Hatch\n4. Bill Flack\n5. Barb Mellers\n6. Wharton Super Forecasting Team members\n7. George Mason University forecasters\n\nThe concept of superforecasters comes from Tetlock's research on individuals who consistently demonstrate exceptional predictive accuracy across various domains. These individuals typically:\n\n- Have above-average analytical skills\n- Are curious and open-minded\n- Update their predictions based on new information\n- Avoid confirmation bias\n- Think in probabilistic terms\n- Are willing to admit when they're wrong\n\nIf you're looking for a comprehensive list, I recommend reading Tetlock's book \"Superforecasting: The Art and Science of Prediction\" for more detailed information about specific superforecasters.",
